{[%evp 0,37,16,28,29,-16,63,54,45,58,60,10,49,57,57,42,79,67,52,27,30,47,52,41,
87,71,127,17,79,57,92,73,80,49,0,-10,-10,-14,11,10]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3
d5 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. h4 O-O 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. h5 {The most consistent move. White is
trying to open the h-file.} c5 {Black should attack the center as soon as
possible.} ({In case of} 7... Bg4 8. hxg6 hxg6 {This position occurred in the
top-level game Morozevich, A - Gelfand, B. Here, I recommend the pawn
sacrifice:} 9. Nh2 $1 $146 Bf5 10. e4 $1 Nxc3 11. bxc3 Bxe4 12. Ng4 {with a
promising initiative for White.}) 8. hxg6 hxg6 9. Bh6 {The exchange of
dark-squared bishops is annoying for Black.} Bxh6 10. Rxh6 Nxc3 ({It is
curious to follow a correspondence game:} 10... Nc6 11. Qd2 cxd4 12. Nxd5 Qxd5
13. Rh8+ $1 Kxh8 14. Qh6+ Kg8 15. Ng5 Qa5+ $1 16. Kd1 Qxg5 17. Qxg5 $14 {
Black has a rook, a knight and a pawn for the queen, but he is, obviously,
fighting for a draw. A queen is a queen! In the current game Meyner,H (2372)
-Ralls, R (2341) LSS email 2013 (½-½, 44) Black indeed managed to hold, but
in over the board game white's chances to score a full point are reasonable
realistic.}) 11. bxc3 Kg7 (11... cxd4 12. Qd2 Kg7 13. Rd1 {transposes}) 12. Qd2
{White doesn't have a huge attack against the black king as there is a
satisfactory defensive resource Rh8 available. However, without the
dark-squared bishop Black can't create pressure along the diagonal h8-a1 and
therefore loses a serious part of his active counterplay.} cxd4 13. Rd1 (13.
Rh4 Rh8 14. Rxh8 Qxh8 15. cxd4 Nc6 16. d5 $6 (16. Rb1 $14 {It would be useful
to move the rook away from the diagonal h8-a1 and at the same time put
pressure along the "b" file.}) 16... Kg8 17. Rc1 Ne5 18. Qc3 Nxf3+ 19. gxf3 Qh1
$132 {1/2-1/2 (43) Tari,A (2599)-Gordievsky,D (2622) Wijk aan Zee 2018}) (13.
cxd4 Nc6 14. Rh4 Qa5 15. e4 Rd8 16. Qxa5 Nxa5 17. Kd2 $14 {1-0 (47) Akobian,V 
(2632)-Mikhalevski,V (2526) Temecula 2015}) 13... Qa5 14. Nxd4 Nc6 15. Nxc6
bxc6 16. Rh4 g5 17. Ra4 Qe5 (17... Qxa4 $2 18. Qxg5+ Kh7 19. Rd4 $18) 18. Qd4
Qxd4 19. cxd4 {White has a slight edge in the endgame thanks to the superior
pawn structure. Black managed to hold in the encounter Li,C (2735)-Svidler,P 
(2749) Geneva 2017 (½-½, 42).} *

