The main move} 8... O-O {is dealt with in chapters 6 and 7.}) 9. Nxb5 O-O ({
After} 9... Qa5+ {a nice game was played by GM Michael Prusikin:} 10. Nc3 Nd7
11. Bd2 Ba6 12. g4 Nhf6 13. Bh3 h5 14. gxh5 Rxh5 $6 (14... Nxh5 15. Qc2 $14 {
followed by castling to the kingside. The white king will be reasonably safe
there which can't be said about his counterpart.}) 15. Bxd7+ Nxd7 16. Rxh5 gxh5
17. Ng5 Ne5 18. Qxh5 Qb6 19. Ne6 $16 {1-0 (46) Prusikin,M (2524)-Jansa,V (2438)
Bayerisch Eisenstein 2014}) ({The move} 9... Bg4 {usually transposes to the
main line after} 10. Bxc4 O-O ({An independent option would be} 10... Nd7 11.
Qc2 Bxf3 12. gxf3 O-O 13. f4 {White's bishop pair and strong pawn center gives
him a more promising position.})) 10. Bxc4 Bg4 ({After} 10... Nd7 {which was
played by MVL and Ganguly, I recommend} 11. Kf1 $1 $146 {Of course, White
shouldn't castle to the kingside. Instead, he is planning to make use of the
h-file.} (11. Qc2 {is also not bad.}) 11... Ba6 (11... Ne5 $6 12. Nxe5 Bxe5 13.
Rxh5 $1 gxh5 14. Qxh5 {is great for White.}) 12. a4 Nb6 13. Be2 $16) 11. Qc2 a6
(11... Na6 12. Be3 Nc7 13. Nc3 $14) (11... Bxf3 12. gxf3 Nd7 13. f4 Qb8 14. e5
$6 (14. f5 $1 {is a better way. White has one more "f" pawn, which is
important, as Black doesn't get the e5 square forever.} Qe5 (14... a6 15. Nc3
$14) 15. Kf1 Nb6 16. Be2 Nf4 17. Rh4 Nxe2 18. Qxe2 $14 {White's kingside
initiative can become dangerous.}) 14... Nb6 15. Be3 Qb7 $13 {0-1 (34)
Kaczmarczyk,D (2423)-Renet,O (2532) Switzerland 2018}) 12. Nc3 (12. Na3 {
also makes some sense. White wants to bring the knight to c4. However, Black
can get a counterplay.} Bxf3 13. gxf3 Qc7 (13... Nd7 $6 14. f4 $14) 14. Kf1 Nd7
15. Rb1 Nb6 16. Be2 f5 17. Nc4 Nxc4 18. Bxc4 Kh8 $13) 12... Bxf3 13. gxf3 Qd6 {
Black is trying to create a blockade on the dark squares.} 14. Ne2 {This is
the most precise move. White is fighting against the blockade and preparing to
move his center forward.} Nd7 15. f4 Nb6 16. e5 Qd7 17. Be3 Nxc4 (17... Rfb8
18. b3 Rb7 19. Qe4 Nxc4 20. bxc4 Rab8 21. Rc1 $14 {1-0 (41) Hakobyan,A (2449)
-Kulaots,K (2597) Minsk 2017}) 18. Qxc4 Rfb8 19. b3 Rb4 20. Qxc5 Rb5 21. Qc6
Qxd5 22. Rc1 $14 {White was pushing in the game Dragnev,V (2466)-Gopal,G (2593)
Caleta 2018 (½-½, 77). Black's knight is basically out of play.} *

