13... Qa5 14. Qd2 Bf5 15. Rc1 Rac8 16. f3 (16. c4 Qxd2+ 17. Kxd2 dxc4 18. Bxc4
Rfd8 19. Bd3 Bxd3 20. Kxd3 {This endgame should end in a draw, but White can
push a little thanks to his better control over the center.}) 16... Rc6 17. g4
Be6 18. hxg6 fxg6 19. Qh2 Bg8 20. Qe5+ Kf7 {Looks scary for Black, but the
cold-blooded engine shows the evaluation 0.00 here!} *

